# Text-Muted Rule

- **Main Rule**: NEVER use the `text-muted` Bootstrap utility class in this project. **NEVER use Bootstrap's `form-text` class** - it applies grey color by default making text unreadable. **NEVER under any circumstance use opacity utilities (`opacity-75`, `opacity-50`, `opacity-25`, etc.) on text elements.** Text must be fully readable and fully opaque.

- **Problem:**
  - `text-muted` applies a light gray color (`#6c757d` in Bootstrap) that has poor contrast on dark backgrounds
  - **Bootstrap's `form-text` class applies grey color by default** - makes helper text unreadable on dark backgrounds
  - **Opacity utilities on text make it unreadable, hard to see, and inaccessible**
  - This creates accessibility issues and poor readability
  - Dark backgrounds require lighter text colors, not muted gray or faded text

- **Solution:**
  - **Use plain, fully opaque text** - no opacity utilities on any text elements
  - For dark backgrounds, use `text-white` or `text-light` (fully opaque, no opacity)
  - For light backgrounds, use default text color (fully opaque, no opacity)
  - **NEVER use Bootstrap's `form-text` class** - it applies grey color by default making text unreadable
  - Helper text should use plain `<div>` or `<p>` with readable text - NOT `<small class="form-text">`
  - On dark backgrounds, helper text must use `text-white` or `text-light` to be readable
  - Descriptions, labels, and all text content must be fully readable - no opacity, no form-text, no grey color

- **Examples:**

  ```html
  <!-- ❌ DON'T: Never use text-muted -->
  <div class="bg-dark">
      <p class="text-muted">This is hard to read</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="card bg-primary text-white">
      <p class="text-muted">Poor contrast here</p>
  </div>
  
  <!-- ❌ DON'T: NEVER use opacity on text - makes it unreadable -->
  <div class="bg-dark">
      <p class="text-white opacity-75">Faded and unreadable</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="card">
      <p class="opacity-75">Faded text - unreadable</p>
  </div>
  
  <small class="form-text opacity-75">Helper text with opacity - unreadable</small>
  
  <small class="form-text">Helper text with form-text class - Bootstrap applies grey color, unreadable</small>
  
  <div class="opacity-75">Any text with opacity - unreadable</div>
  
  <!-- ✅ DO: Use fully readable, fully opaque text -->
  <div class="bg-dark">
      <p class="text-white">Readable on dark</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="card bg-primary text-white">
      <p>Readable text</p>
  </div>
  
  <!-- ✅ DO: Plain readable text on light backgrounds -->
  <div class="card">
      <p>Readable text on light background</p>
  </div>
  
  <!-- ✅ DO: Helper text - use plain div or p, NOT form-text class -->
  <div class="mt-1">Readable helper text (no form-text class)</div>
  
  <!-- ✅ DO: Helper text on dark background -->
  <div class="bg-dark">
      <div class="mt-1 text-white">Readable helper text on dark background</div>
  </div>
  
  <div>Plain readable text</div>
  ```

- **When to Use:**
  - **Light backgrounds**: Use default text color (fully opaque, no opacity utilities, no text-muted)
  - **Dark backgrounds**: Use `text-white` or `text-light` (fully opaque, no opacity utilities)
  - **Colored backgrounds**: Use appropriate text color class (`text-white`, `text-light`) without opacity
  - **Helper text**: Use plain readable text - `<div class="mt-1">Helper text here</div>` NOT `<small class="form-text">` - Bootstrap's form-text applies grey color
  - **NEVER use Bootstrap's `form-text` class** - it makes text grey and unreadable
  - **Helper text on dark backgrounds**: Use `<div class="mt-1 text-white">Helper text</div>` - always explicitly readable
  - **Descriptions**: Use fully readable text - no opacity utilities
  - **All text**: Must be fully opaque and readable - no exceptions

- **Bootstrap Text Color Classes (NO OPACITY):**
  - `text-white` - White text for dark backgrounds (fully opaque)
  - `text-light` - Light gray text for dark backgrounds (fully opaque)
  - Default text color - For light backgrounds (fully opaque)
  
- **NEVER USE ON TEXT (NO EXCEPTIONS):**
  - `opacity-75`, `opacity-50`, `opacity-25` - Makes text unreadable
  - `text-muted` - Poor contrast on dark backgrounds
  - `form-text` - Bootstrap class that applies grey color by default, making text unreadable
  - Any opacity utility combined with text elements
  - Grey/unreadable helper text - use plain readable text instead
  - **Placeholder text in form inputs** - must be readable (CSS handles this in `bootstrap-overrides.css` - placeholders use `var(--text-light)`)
  - **Default select option text** - must be readable (CSS handles this in `bootstrap-overrides.css` - default options use `var(--text-light)`)

- **Accessibility:**
  - Always ensure sufficient contrast ratio (WCAG AA minimum 4.5:1 for normal text)
  - Test text readability on both light and dark backgrounds
  - Use browser dev tools to check contrast ratios
  - Text must be fully readable - opacity reduces readability and accessibility

- **Enforcement:**
  - NEVER use `text-muted` in this project
  - **NEVER under any circumstance use opacity utilities (`opacity-75`, `opacity-50`, `opacity-25`, etc.) on text elements**
  - Text must be fully readable - no fading, no muting, no opacity
  - Replace any existing instances with fully readable, fully opaque text
  - Verify contrast ratios meet accessibility standards
  - Helper text and descriptions must use plain readable text with no opacity, no form-text class
  - **NEVER use Bootstrap's `form-text` class** - use `<div class="mt-1">Helper text</div>` instead for readable helper text
  - **Placeholder text and default select options** - CSS in `bootstrap-overrides.css` ensures these are readable with `var(--text-light)` color
  - Example: `<small class="form-text">` is WRONG - Bootstrap makes it grey. Use `<div class="mt-1">Helper text</div>` instead for fully readable text
  - Example: Placeholder text in inputs is handled by CSS - never override with grey/unreadable colors
